# ZENO commit message format:
# <type>: <English summary>
# add:<PhaseNum><English summary>  # Phase completion only
#
# Write the actual commit message above these comments.
#
# Rules:
# - Write the summary in English.
# - Use a half-width colon immediately after type.
# - Put exactly one half-width space after type:.
# - Do not put a space between type and colon.
# - Do not use feat. Use add for new features.
# - For Phase completion commits, use add:<PhaseNum><English summary>.
# - Do not put a space after add: in Phase completion commits.
# - Write all public-facing materials in English, including tracked docs,
#   README.md, and source code comments.
#
# Allowed types:
# fix: Bug fix
# hotfix: Critical bug fix
# add: New feature
# update: Feature update, existing feature improvement, or non-bug change
# change: Specification change
# clean: Cleanup, refactor, or readability improvement
# disable: Disable, comment out, or temporarily pause
# remove: File removal or obsolete feature removal
# upgrade: Version or dependency upgrade
# revert: Revert a previous change
#
# Good examples:
# fix: Fix crash on startup
# add: Add 2D rendering API
# add:44 Package SDK distribution
# update: Update sample game rendering
# clean: Remove stale comments and duplicated logic
